 his mind, “Don’t be afraid little one.  I will not harm you.”<br><br>Muffin squeaked in acknowledgement.<br><br>“Yes, it seems that we have a lot of work ahead of Muffin.  But, we must run and help our friends from this impending danger,” Inien walked from outside the circle of books and stepped outside.  “Come on small one, we must go.”<br><br>Muffin followed his master outside.  He flapped over the wall and next to Inien’s leg.  He gripped it tightly, happy to see his master back on his feet.<br><br>Inien looked down at Muffin and smiled, “To Qeynos first.  We have a small affair to attend to quickly.”<br><br>[ In an underground cave ]<br><br>Cendarien looked out to see the sisters prepare to engage in battle.  He glanced over at Phelsuma who had fallen to the ground.  He ran to her side and bent low, “What is wrong?”<br><br>“I’m ashamed of what I have done.  I won’t be able to ever show my face.  The evil that I have perpetrated on others is unforgivable.  It will be hard to forget,” Phelsuma looked up at Cendarien.  She wiped away a stray tear.  Her long blonde hair lay matted in her face.<br><br>“Phelsuma, don’t worry.  You were not of your right mind.  How could you have ever known of what you did,” Cendarien reached down and grabbed her hands.  “It might be hard for you to forget.  But I guarantee that they will forgive you once the truth be known.”<br><br>Phelsuma looked up.  She sniffed quietly, “You think so?”<br><br>Cendarien smiled, “I know so.  Come on hun.  It is time to help our friends.”<br><br>Cendarien helped Phelsuma to her feet.  She pushed her hair back from her face and wiped the dried tears from her face.  Cendarien peered out once more to see what was going on once more.<br><br>Belana brought her dagger’s points towards the underside of her forearms.  She pointed the tips towards her elbows creating a barrier of metal to protect her flesh.<br><br>Darkpoint was on top of Belana and swung the sword vertically at Belana.  Belana quickly brought her hands up blocking the blow with her make shift gauntlets.  She jumped back from the blow and backed away.  Darkpoint followed again attacking first.  The sound of metal against metal echoed through the cavern.<br><br>“I can’t let this happen,” Cendarien stood up.  He ran out from beside the wall and towards his friends.  Phelsuma followed.<br><br>The dark figure looked on towards the ensuing battle between the demon and Belana.  He smiled.  The plan had been followed perfectly.  He had her in his reach.  Even if she managed to beat the demon, he would finish her off himself.<br><br>Cendarien was almost upon the dark figure before he turned around and saw him.  The figure raised his arms and quickly fired the same webbing that snared Kelwin.  Cendarien dodged the blast.  The figure quickly summoned forth another bolt but to no avail.  Cendarien hit the figure with his fist across the cheek sending him sprawling.  Phelsuma followed behind and turned towards Kelwin.  She began to work on his bindings.<br><br>“I’m going to free you then were all getting out of here,” Phelsuma said.<br><br>“You will get no argument from me,” Kelwin replied.<br><br>Belana flipped backwards avoiding the blade of her attacker.  She had yet struck out with any offense.  She glanced over at her friends.<br><br>Cendarien stood above the dark figure.  He reached down and grabbed him with both hands around the collar of the cloak he wore.  Cendarien let loose another strike with his fist sending the figure to the ground again.<br><br>Belana turned back to dodge the next blow from Darkpoint.  Frustration seemed to cross her face, she was becoming annoyed by Belana’s tactics.  Darkpoint stopped chasing the rogue and turned towards his master.  Cendarien again was picking up the figures body from the ground preparing for another strike.  Darkpoint sheathed his sword quickly and began to run towards Cendarien.<br><br>“Cendarien!” Belana shouted.<br><br>Cendarien turned away from his enemy to see Darkpoint charging towards him.  The sight of seeing Whitepoint’s body drawing nearer caused him to stutter in his movement.  The dark figured capitalized and swept Cendarien’s legs out from under him.  Cendarien hit the ground back first.  The figure jumped on top of him and landed a right cross on Cendarien’s face.  The figure rolled off Cendarien’s body and rose to his feet.  He wiped the blood away that had begun to pool from inside his mouth.<br><br>Kelwin noticed the figure bearing his sight on them, “Phelsuma!  Watch it.”<br><br>Phelsuma turned to look at the figure.  She hadn’t been able to free Kelwin yet from his bindings.  She stood up and began to cast a spell.  The figure looked down at Cendarien’s body.  He was beginning to regain his composure.  The figure grabbed his body with one hand and with a  great showing of strength held Cendarien’s body off the ground with one hand.  He then tossed it towards Phelsuma.  She quickly stopped chanting and braced herself to catch the flying wood elf.  Cendarien struck Phelsuma and they both went tumbling across the cavern floor.  Phelsuma struck the backside of her head against the hard rock of the cave knocking her unconscious.<br><br>Belana turned and ran towards her friends.  Darkpoint unsheathed her sword once more and gave chase to Belana.  Belana shot a glance back towards her adversaries and noticed Darkpoint closing in on her.  She drew her daggers back once more and jumped forward quickly.  She landed facing the other way and charged forward towards Darkpoint.  She thought in her head quickly, “Please forgive me sister.”  She struck out at Darkpoint with both her blades but Darkpoint parried the blow.  Belana fell back from the force of the attack.<br><br>Darkpoint turned towards Belana and struck down with his sword to fallen rogue.  Belana quickly rolled to her right avoiding the blow.  A flash of sparks shot from the ground as Darkpoint’s sword struck.  Belana flipped herself forward back to her feet.<br><br>The dark figure walked towards the three friends on the ground.  He looked down at the unconscious druid.  He moved his sight towards the ensnared ranger and shook his head.  Cendarien struggled to his feet once more.  The dark figure produced a small dagger from inside his cloak and approached the unsuspecting ranger.  Kelwin’s eyes noticed the weapon.<br><br>“Cendarien!” Kelwin yelled.<br><br>Belana turned her attention to the shout and noticed the figure drawing near to Cendarien.  Darkpoint turned to face her once more and brought his sword back up into an attack style.  Cendarien tried to shake off his dizziness.  The robed figure showed his intentions and brought his armed hand back for the final blow.<br><br>Belana brought her daggers up into a throwing position and threw them towards the dark figure.  The first whistled by the figures head and missed.  The second one found its mark on the figures vulnerable arm.  The blade sank deep.  Crying out, the figure dropped his weapon.  Cendarien realizing his predicament grabbed the falling dagger from the air.  He turned quickly with the blade jutting out from his hand and caught the figure in the midsection with dagger.  The figure let loose a howl.  Cendarien met the figures gaze.  His white eyes began to loose their color quickly.  His face began to contort into an array of different colors.  Cendarien let loose the blade and stood above the figure.  He clutched the dagger buried in his body and fell to the ground.  Life soon left his body causing only momentary spasms to echo through body.<br><br>Cendarien turned towards his wife.  A smile of satisfaction crossed his face as he gazed at her.  She answered him with the roguish smirk he had gotten so many times in their youth.  It revitalized his soul to see her like that once more.  It had been a dreary time for both of them.  Seeing her smile again made this all seem worth it.<br><br>Then Cendarien’s smile left.<br><br>Belana turned around and felt an uneasiness inside her.  An explosion of breath escaped from her body.  She lurched backward but did not fall.  Belana looked down to see Darkpoint’s sword running through her body.  She glanced up to see the cold eye’s of her sister.  They were dark.  Cold.  She blinked to somehow dispel this reality.  She tried to speak but a sputter was all she could muster.  A trail of her own blood bubbled up from her throat and leaked from the corner of her mouth.  Her head tilted as she felt her life force begin to leave her.  Darkpoint withdrew the sword from her body.  The troubling sound of steel on flesh radiated inside the cavern for all to hear.  Belana stood in front of her sister.  Her arms hung at her side as if someone had tied a great weight to them.  She took a step forward but her body could not support her.  Belana fell to her knees, and then to her side.<br><br>Cendarien ran forward.<br><br>Darkpoint looked down at the sword covered in the blood of Blackpoint.  A sudden eruption from inside Whitepoint's body caused her body to stiffen.  He let go of the sword as a warm feeling began to build inside.  Whitepoint’s body began to pulse with a bright light.  The outline of a figure began to permeate off of Whitepoint’s body.  It stepped away revealing the form of the rogue that Belana had killed months ago.  Whitepoint’s body fell to the ground.  Discarded by the demon at last.<br><br>The deed had been done.  The quest for resurrection had ended.  The dark rogue turned to the two sisters.  Their bodies both lying in front of each others.  His body began to fade away as it journeyed to find wherever his original body had been laid to rest.<br><br>Belana gazed forward as the body of her sister fell in front of her gaze.  Her face was no longer darkened or disfigured.  The golden white flesh tone returned.  Belana smiled.  She inhaled one last time and spoke, “I will see you soon.”  She outstretched her hand towards her sisters.  She gripped the soft fingertips and squeezed.  Belana felt a slight smile cross her face, but it soon faded away as her face grew placid.  Belana sighed.<br><br>Cendarien pulled her gaze away from her sisters.  He cradled her head towards his and saw the streak of blood that ran from her mouth.  Belana slowly exhaled as her body became heavy.  Cendarien looked down at her wound and realized that it was to late to save her.  He brought her head up to his shoulder and held her close burying his head into her hair as he felt the rush of death pass over her.<br> <p><img src="http://home.insightbb.com/~blackpoint/AnimationEQ.gif" height=85 width=468 alt="Blackpoint Sorrowblade Thistletongue" border=0></a></p><span class=m><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bebonmoon.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blackpointsorrowbladethistletongue>Blackpoint Sorrowblade Thistletongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/20/02 3:24:09 am<br></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>429</b>  </span></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=33.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/email.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="email this topic to a friend" align=absmiddle></a> Email This To a Friend </td><td align=right valign="top"></td></tr></table><table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor=#006400><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding="5" cellspacing="1"><tr><td nowrap bgcolor=#000000 width=20%><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm2.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><img src=http://ebonmoon.com/images/Icons/newtopic.gif border=0 alt="New Topic"></a>  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a self href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?top